\cf1\ul PHILOSOPHY\ulnone :\ul\par
\par
\ulnone The Mariemont Community Church Extended Care is a Christian school.  We include basic Christian truths with basic educational skills in the preparation of our Extended care children for their formal education.\par
The Extended Care is an outreach ministry of the church, which states the following purposes in its charter:\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\li300\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li660\tx660 1.\tab To operate the extended care; serve sacrificially on Christ\rquote s behalf toward extended care children and their families from Mariemont and neighboring communities.\par
2.\tab To demonstrate the love of Christ in the way faculty and staff work together and the way they serve the extended care\rquote s children and families.\par
3.\tab To operate in a way that demonstrates excellence and wholeheartedness befitting followers of Christ.\par
4.\tab To be a light of Christ to extended care children and their families.  As a result of connection with the extended care, children and family members will be drawn closer to Christ.\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\par
Additionally, the goal of the Mariemont Community Church Extended Care is to promote intellectual, physical, social, emotional, and spiritual growth of our students by: \par

\pard\nowidctlpar\li300\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li660\tx660 1.\tab Providing a school with a planned environment and curriculum, where learning takes place in a nurturing atmosphere.        \par

\pard 
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnindent60\pnstart2\pndec{\pntxta.}}
\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li660\tx660   Encouraging each child in self-discovery, furthering their understanding of his/her value to the family and community.\par
{\pntext\f0 3.\tab}  Preparing each student for further education by allowing the individual child to develop at his/her own pace through sensory experiences, exploration and creative activities.\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li660\tx660 4.\tab Relating simple Christian truths, principles and values to the lives of extended care children.\par

