\par
2.\ul Severe Weather Emergencies\ulnone .  Severe Weather emergency drills will be conducted once a month during the months of April, May, August and September.\par

\pard\nowidctlpar\tx4680 In the event of severe weather conditions such as tornadoes, thunderstorms, major snowfall, blizzards, ice storms, or earthquakes occure before school begins, parents should use their judgment.  If severe weather occurs while the children are attending school, the teachers will take attendance and lead the children out of the classroom and place them in the main hallway, where the cubbies are located. This area has been approved by the fire department as a safe place for the children to be during severe weather conditions.  Parents will be called and notified to come and pick up their child. \ul In the event of snow, the preschool will be closed if Mariemont City Schools are either delayed or cancelled.\ulnone   Please listen to one of the local radio or television stations for the announcement.  A preschool closing will not be announced separately. \par
\par
